[[image:Mater Verborum.jpg|thumb|Title page of «Mater Verborum»]]
'''Mater Verborum''' (or '''Glosa Salomonis''') is a medieval encyclopedical dictionary written in [[Latin language]] around 1240. The document is especially renowned for more than 1000 comments written in it in the medieval [[Czech language]]. The manuscript is deposited in the [[Library of the National Museum]] (Prague), under signature X A 11.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.manuscriptorium.com/apps/main/index.php?request=request_document&docId=set04071382|title=Mater verborum (tzv. Glosa Salomonis)|publisher=manuscriptorium.com|language=Czech|accessdate=27 March 2013}}</ref>
